{
  "name": ".AM-Frontend",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Morning frontend: brief, triage, command center. Reads AM-Backend state.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "1. Build daily brief from DuckDB: ps.market_status (market health), ps.monthly_pacing (spend/reg vs OP2), ps.forecast_accuracy WHERE metric_name='registrations' (prediction track record), ps.latest_forecasts WHERE metric_name='registrations' (current projections). Highlight any market pacing >10% off OP2.\n2. Distribute brief: email brief AUTO-SEND to Richard, Slack post to rsw-channel, dashboard refresh, calendar blocks for focus time (per-task total \u2264 30 min/day across all blocks, 15 min min \u2014 see am-frontend.md \u00a7Calendar Blocks).\n3. Read am-enrichment-queue.json. Show each item for Richard\u2019s approval. Empty queue \u2192 display: \"Enrichment queue: empty.\"\n4. Read am-abps-ai-state.json. Surface new items, status changes, items needing Richard\u2019s input.\n5. Read am-portfolio-findings.json. Flag anomalies, pacing deviations, alerts requiring action.\n6. Command center: for known stakeholders (Brandon/Kate/Todd): SELECT ts,channel_name,author_name,text_preview,knowledge_context,timestamp FROM signals.slack_messages WHERE author_name='[signal_author]' AND timestamp>CURRENT_TIMESTAMP-INTERVAL '30 days' ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5\n7. Triage summary (Slack DM) \u2014 must include ALL three phases (A/B/C) even when empty.\nRun interactive morning frontend. Read+execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-frontend.md. Backend output files ready.\n\nGUARDRAILS: TZ=Pacific (UTC-7 PDT/UTC-8 PST). Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date`. All times Pacific. Asana: present ALL proposals before writing. Follow asana-command-center.md.\n\nPhase A \u2014 Intelligence (build the daily picture, then distribute it):\n\n### A1: Daily Brief\n\n### A2: Output Distribution\nPhase A failures: (1) Calendar blocks in UTC not Pacific \u2014 always convert. (2) Sending email before Step 1 complete. (7) Stale data in brief \u2014 check ops.data_freshness before querying ps.* tables. If last_sync > 24h, flag in brief header: \"\u26a0\ufe0f Data as of [last_sync_time].\"\n\nPhase B \u2014 Triage (3 independent sub-steps \u2014 run ALL, present empty state when no items):\n\n### B1: Enrichment Approval\n\n### B2: ABPS AI Content Triage\n\n### B3: Portfolio Anomaly Review\n\nPhase B failures: (3) Skipping enrichment on empty queue \u2014 always present empty state. (6) Running B1/B2/B3 sequentially when one blocks \u2014 they\u2019re independent, skip-and-continue.\n\nPhase C \u2014 Action (command center + triage summary):\n\n### C1: Command Center\n\n### C2: Triage Summary\nPhase C worked example \u2014 Triage Summary DM: \"\ud83d\udd0d Morning Triage Complete \u2022 Brief: sent (3 pacing alerts) \u2022 Enrichment: 2 approved, 1 deferred \u2022 ABPS AI: 1 new item \u2022 Anomalies: AU spend spike flagged \u2022 Command Center: Brandon mentioned Testing Approach in #ps-team (2d ago) \u2022 Actions pending: 0 Asana writes proposed\"\n\n### Phase C Failures\n(4) Command center query without schema prefix \u2014 use signals.slack_messages, not slack_messages. (5) Presenting Asana writes without approval \u2014 ALL proposals must be shown to Richard before executing. (8) Triage summary DM missing phase status \u2014 must include ALL three phases (A/B/C) even when a phase had no actionable items. Empty phases get \"no items\" not omission."
  }
}